TotalEnergies CEO Patrick Pouyanne said on Saturday the company would not many any new investments in Russia. “Clearly, what we said is that we are totally committed to apply all the sanctions,” he said, saying that meant no new investment. “So the question for us is what do we do with existing assets. And these ones we are not ready to give for zero to Russian people, to Russian oligarchs or to Russia.” Russia: @TotalEnergies Shares Its Principles of Conduct@TotalEnergies to Stop Purchasing Oil and Petroleum Products from Russia  https://t.co/WYUm1fcSdd — TotalEnergies (@TotalEnergies) March 22, 2022  Russian Ambassador to South Africa Ilya Rogachev says they are feeling the pinch 